subSubSection.paragraph:
Colour in life (based on 
type
series).

Ground colour of dorsum yellowish brown to greenish-brown. A continuous series of 6–9 dark brown blotches extend laterally from behind the eye to vent (
Fig. 3
). The blotches vary in shape, but are mostly elongate and run parallel to body axis. A maximum of three rows of such blotches can be seen around midbody, and are largest medially. Typically, two triangular shaped blotches in interorbital region, each in contact with upper eyelid (
Fig. 3
). A dark brown streak runs from behind the nostril to the eye and continues from behind the eye to angle of jaws. Iris golden brown, tympanum dark brown (
Fig. 3
). Upper lip cream coloured. Dorsal surface in forelimb and hindlimb is lighter compared to colouration of dorsum, dorsum with distinct broad bands of dark brown colour. Back of thigh with yellowish brown blotches, forming a reticulate pattern (
Fig. 6
). Similar reticulated pattern are present on region between axilla and groin. A narrow dark brown line runs along outer edge of forearm and tarsus. Venter cream-coloured. Gular region yellowish-white, sometimes with a light reticulate pattern.
